# Frontend Design System

**For all component examples, class names, variants, and usage patterns, refer to [`docs/ui-kit.html`](../../docs/ui-kit.html).**

## Stack

- **Tailwind CSS 4.0** via `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin
- **DaisyUI 5.x** via `@plugin "daisyui"` in `app.css`
- **Alpine.js** for lightweight JS interactions
- **Livewire 3.5+** for server-driven dynamic components

## Core Principles

- DaisyUI 5 is the primary component library. Tailwind CSS 4 utilities customize and extend it.
- Zero external CSS. No `@apply`. No hand-rolled color values when a semantic token exists.
- Use `data-theme="securecat"` on `<html>` (already configured).

## Component Priority Order

1. **DaisyUI component classes** — `btn`, `card`, `table`, `alert`, `modal`, `input`, `select`, etc.
2. **Tailwind utilities** — extend DaisyUI with spacing, sizing, responsive breakpoints
3. **Reusable Blade components** — wrap repeated patterns in `resources/views/components/`
4. **Livewire components** — for interactive/stateful UI needing server roundtrips
5. **Raw CSS** — only as last resort; never use `@apply`

## DaisyUI 5 Breaking Changes (from v4)

**Do NOT use these v4 class names:**

| Removed (v4)           | Use Instead (v5)                                    |
|------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
| `form-control`         | `fieldset` class on `<fieldset>` element            |
| `label-text`           | `label` class on `<label>` element                  |
| `input-bordered`       | Not needed — `input` has border by default           |
| `select-bordered`      | Not needed — `select` has border by default          |
| `card-bordered`        | `card-border`                                        |
| `card-compact`         | `card-sm`                                            |
| `btn-group`            | `join` + `join-item` on children                     |
| `input-group`          | `join` + `join-item` on children                     |
| Table row `hover`      | `hover:bg-base-300` on `<tr>`                        |
| `btm-nav`              | `dock`                                               |

## Project-Specific Patterns

- **Forms:** Use `<fieldset class="fieldset">` with `<label class="label">` for fields. See [`docs/ui-kit.html`](../../docs/ui-kit.html) for examples.
- **Blade components:** Place in `resources/views/components/` (kebab-case naming).
- **Livewire:** Use `wire:model` on DaisyUI form elements; `wire:loading` with DaisyUI `loading` component.
- **Alpine.js:** Drives client-only interactions (modals, dropdowns, tabs).

## What NOT to Do

- No hand-rolled buttons/inputs — use DaisyUI components
- No arbitrary color values — use DaisyUI semantic tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-base-content`, etc.)
- No `@apply` — compose with utility classes directly
- No external CSS files beyond `app.css`
- No v4 class names (see breaking changes above)
- No inline `<style>` blocks in Blade templates
- No Bootstrap, Bulma, or other CSS frameworks — DaisyUI + Tailwind only

